  childSummary:"Your phone talks to a nearby cell tower using invisible radio waves — like a walkie-talkie but MUCH more powerful! The whole country is divided into 'cells' — each with its own tower. When you move (walking, driving), your phone smoothly switches from one tower to the next without you noticing. 5G is the newest version — it's 10-100 times FASTER than 4G because: it uses WIDER radio channels (like a wider road carrying more cars), it has SMARTER antennas with 64-128 parts that can aim radio waves directly at YOUR phone like a spotlight (instead of blasting in all directions like a light bulb), and it can create separate 'lanes' for different uses (one lane for movies, another for doctors doing surgery remotely). India has rolled out 5G in 700+ cities — and you get it at NO extra cost on your regular Jio or Airtel plan!",
